Given just a stacktrace of a box that is performing poorly or generating errors, it is impossible to determine the runtime state of the JIRA instance.  For instance, a CVS parse might have been running in the background creating a low memory condition, or there may have been a sudden spike in the number of users.  It would be very helpful if some vital statistics (memory, user count etc) were, eg:

2005-03-07 13:02:46,052 ERROR [core.util.thumbnail.Thumber] [510/512Mb,100u] Unable to create thumbnail image of attachment with ....

See the stat4j project (http://www.devx.com/Java/Article/22110/1954?pf=true) for some other ideas in this area.

