Currently, the 'Reporter' field is required by default.  When a JIRA admin the grants 'Anyone' the permission to create issues, this doesn't have the desired effect - the create issue page dies with a 'Reporter is required' error.

While we can't enforce logical consistency of admin settings, we can at least warn about likely inconsistencies such as this one.

It would be nice to be able to add a new view without changing the source. For example, on the issue navigator, I would like to design other views. These can be easily added to the .jsp and added to actions.xml. The problem is the following code in the IssueNavigator class:

if ("rss".equalsIgnoreCase(view))
  return "rss";
else if ("excel".equalsIgnoreCase(view))
  return "excel";
else if ("full".equalsIgnoreCase(view))
  return "full";
else
  return getResult();

If this was changed to the following, it would allow this flexibility:

if (view.length() > 0)
  return view.toLowerCase();
else
  return getResult();

