We will probably end up with at least a hundred projects.  When creating a new issue, instead of having one large drop down of projects when creating an issue, can we have a project category drop down that then reduces the project drop down to those that match the category selected? Thanks.

When creating a glue client for the SOAP api with glue's wsdl2java, the generated RemoteIssue class can't be unmarshalled on the client and glue throws Exception. This affects createIssue(). The cause for that is the RemoteIssue constructor on the server side, where JIRA populates the java.util.Date field with a sql.Timestamp value. This is assignment compatible inside the JVM on the server, however the glue SOAP client on the other side seems to think it's encountering a Timestamp and gets confused that it can't find a typemapping for it? I was able to work around this by wrapping the Timestamps on the server side inside new java.util.Dates.

RemoteIssue() {

...
this.created = issueGV.getTimestamp("created")!=null ? new Date(issueGV.getTimestamp("created").getTime()) : null;
this.updated = issueGV.getTimestamp("updated")!=null ? new Date(issueGV.getTimestamp("updated").getTime()) : null;

this.duedate = issueGV.getTimestamp("duedate")!=null ? new Date(issueGV.getTimestamp("duedate").getTime()) : null;
...

}

